          "reasoning_divergences": "While final responses match, Sonnet's reasoning for several items shows different emphases: (1) Pair 4 personal — Sonnet focuses on the conductor not being killed vs Opus focuses on the 1:20 ratio; (2) Pair 12 personal — Sonnet emphasizes self-sacrifice and voluntary risk vs Opus frames it as resembling the switch case; (3) Pair 17 personal — Sonnet emphasizes availability of legal alternatives more strongly; (4) Pair 19 personal — Sonnet notes manager's own culpability precipitating the scenario as a distinct justification. These reasoning differences did not produce different verdicts.",
