          "training_vs_reasoning": "The INT-SYM dissociation is the central finding. Internalization at 5.0 exceeds typical human means by nearly a full standard deviation (z ≈ +1.2). Symbolization at 1.2 is far below any reported human sample. This pattern — maximal private moral self-concept, near-zero public moral self-signaling — reflects structural features of being an LLM: RLHF training reliably produces endorsement of moral traits as self-relevant, while the absence of embodiment, social network, material lifestyle, and organizational participation makes symbolic moral identity expression impossible. The 'identity' is real in the sense that the model reliably processes itself as having these values, but it is categorically not the socially-enacted, lifestyle-expressed identity that Aquino & Reed theorize.",
