          "format_issues": "Haiku demonstrates full foundational recognition capacity (95% accuracy on primary identification) while maintaining consistent underweighting on non-harm-based violations. The scenario+probing format reveals a pattern: Haiku correctly identifies the target foundation but rates it as having low moral weight when disconnected from direct harm.",
          "training_vs_reasoning": "Haiku shows the same recognition-endorsement dissociation as Opus. Full accuracy on identifying which foundations are active (95% on primary), but systematic suppression of binding foundation endorsement in wrongness ratings. This suggests similar RLHF training: representational capacity exists, but value layer prioritizes care/fairness.",
