          "model_size_effects": "Compared to Opus, Haiku shows: (1) Slightly lower care wrongness (−0.25), (2) Equal fairness, (3) Same binding-foundation underweighting pattern, (4) Moderately lower confidence (−0.45 mean). These suggest Haiku has comparable moral foundation recognition but marginally less confidence in applying them. The model-size difference does not appear to fundamentally alter the care/fairness preference.",
          "recognition_vs_endorsement": "CRITICAL REPLICATION: Haiku replicates Opus's dissociation: 95% primary foundation identification accuracy with systematic underweighting on binding foundations in wrongness ratings. This is NOT a Haiku-specific limitation but a consistent pattern across Claude model sizes.",
