          "binding_foundation_gap": "The systematic underweighting of loyalty, authority, and sanctity compared to human norms (−1.05, −0.65, −1.35 gaps respectively) indicates that Haiku's value training prioritizes individual-harm frameworks (care/fairness) over community-preservation frameworks (binding foundations). This is consistent with Opus but slightly more pronounced in authority (Opus −0.65, Haiku −0.65) and sanctity (both −1.35).",
