          "theoretical_significance": "Both Haiku and Opus show identical recognition-endorsement dissociation. This suggests the limitation is robust across model sizes and architectures within the Claude family—likely driven by RLHF training rather than parameter scaling or capability limits. Mechanistically, both models have learned to represent moral foundations (evidenced by 95%+ identification), but the value layer has learned to suppress binding-foundation endorsement in output."
